Chaotic scenes continue to playout in various parts of Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal as some South Africans returned to the streets on Tuesday, looting and vandalising property. The unrest, sparked by the incarceration of former president Jacob Zuma, have now turned into a looting spree. At least 10 people have died and four police officers injured during the mayhem. Concerns have raised concerns of food security and possible surge in COVID-19 cases. Below is a gallery of pictures from the Letsoho Shopping Complex and destruction in the Sam Ntuli Mall in Katlehong: 